KYOTO HOTEL ROUNDUP
where to stay for your next trip to Kyoto, Japan

@capellakyoto - a stunning new opening with a true onsen and daily cultural programming on-site (I toured this but am not allowed to post my photos yet)

@hotel_the_mitsui_kyoto - you need to pick your room wisely but this Japanese-owned hotel has a fascinating history and lovely interior courtyard 

@fskyoto - private gardens within the city center. families should stay here for many reasons, but most of all for the matcha chocolate chip muffins and Japanese fluffy pancakes at breakfast

@sixsenseskyoto - same location as Four Seasons but a much smaller footprint. Love their top suite for families, and it's the only hotel with a dedicated kids club. Great speakeasy bar, which is nice if you like getting a nightcap when the rest of Kyoto is asleep 

@parkhyatttokyo - gorgeous view from the rooms with ideal proximity to tea houses, temples, and specialty shopping 

@acehotelkyoto - buzzy lifestyle hotel with funky Tatami room options, a reliable pick for creatives and younger travelers at a lower price point 

I didn't get to squeeze in tours of @ritzcarltonkyoto, @theshinmonzen, or @aman_kyoto on this trip, but we keep these in our back pocket to drop into client itineraries depending on interests, style, and travel companions. 

